From Xavier:
<<<<
Dear David, Ralf and Sergey,

I have now finished coding, compiling and testing the changes proposed in
the computation of the heat fluxes in SOLPS5.0 to be consistent with the
formulation used in the Russian version (i.e. removing the double-counting
of the energy flows caused by the ExB and diamagnetic terms). This
implicates fives routines:

- B2TFNB, where I now compute, in addition to FNA_32 and FNA_52, the new
arrays FNA_32ND and FNA_52ND (ND for No Drifts).
- B2NEWS which calls B2TFNB, and then computes the secondary quantities
FNI_32, FNI_52, FNE_32 and FNE_52. Please note (there are comments to this
effect in the code), that these four quantities are the flows without the
drifts terms, since it's these we will need later. The code computation
makes this clear. This of course changes some of the diagnostics we had,
which I removed when they stopped making sense. It then calls the modified
other routines.
- B2TFHE and B2TFHI, which now have a clear and explicit computation of the
heat fluxes as:
   (3/2 FN_32 + 5/2 FN_52) + 3/2 F_ExB + 5/2 F_DIA
- In order to compute FNE_32, I had to make sure that FCH_32 was also
computed properly and there I found that the coding was not consistent
between B2TFCH and B2TFHE when computing the electron fluxes. In fact, the
diamagnetic current contribution in B2TFCH was missing a factor of NE (!),
among other troubles. The codings are now consistent, and apparently the
code runs like it a lot better that way. I also now make sure that FCH_32
and FCH_52 are strictly computed without diamagnetic or ExB contributions,
as originally intended.

I also cleaned up the argument lists and switches occurring from the split
between B2TFHE and B2TFHI (back in Sept. 2002 when the mistake was likely
originally introduced). I have checked that, in case without drifts, the
code behaviour is unchanged, but there is certainly a kick to the residuals
for runs with drifts, which should then be revisited. The impact is smallish
in the cases I tested with, but I can't say this will automatically always
be the case.

The modified files are to be found in the usual place, i.e.:
/afs/ipp/u/xpb/solps5.0_drifts/src/Braams/b2/src.local/

Dave, please carry over these changes onto the Master at your convenience,
and publish the text above on solps-users and solps-developers.

Cheers,

Xavier.
