----------- $SOLPSTOP/data.local:

Bulk_properties.name:
---------------------
Data file containing the bulk properties of the material 'name'. 
Currently only Graphite available but will be expanded as data and time become available.
Contains:

'Graphite'          ! material long name (*32)
2.26e3              ! mass density (Kg/m3)
1.3e-5              ! parameter KA for fit of thermal conductivity : 1/(KA*T+KB)
1.6e-3              ! parameter KB for fit of thermal conductivity : 1/(KA*T+KB)
170.7               ! parameter A1 for fit of thermal conductivity : A1 + A2*T + A3*T**2 + A4*T**3
-0.1680             ! parameter A2 for fit of thermal conductivity : A1 + A2*T + A3*T**2 + A4*T**3
6.486e-5            ! parameter A3 for fit of thermal conductivity : A1 + A2*T + A3*T**2 + A4*T**3
-8.854e-9           ! parameter A4 for fit of thermal conductivity : A1 + A2*T + A3*T**2 + A4*T**3
1.47                ! parameter B1 for fit of heat capacity : B1 + B2*T - B3/T**2
3.66e-4             ! parameter B2 for fit of heat capacity : B1 + B2*T - B3/T**2
7.54e4              ! parameter B3 for fit of heat capacity : B1 + B2*T - B3/T**2

The parameters KA and KB are used within the analytical solution of the 0-D temperature equation.
Other parameters matter for the 1-D time-dependent temperature evaolution model.
All units are MKS.

Surface_properties.name:
------------------------
Data file containing the surface properties of the material 'name'. 
Currently only Graphite available but will be expanded as data and time become available.
Contains:

'Graphite'          ! material long name (*32)
1                   ! number of material constituents
6                   ! atomic number of the material constituents (must all be on the same line!)
1                   ! relative abundance of the material constituents (must all be integer)
1.8                 ! chemical sputtering parameter erel
0.9                 ! blackbody emissivity
-40181.0            ! parameter A in the Vapor pressure : 10^(A/T+B)
14.80               ! parameter B in the Vapor pressure : 10^(A/T+B)
0.4                 ! sticking coefficient for vapor pressure calculation
3400.0              ! vaporisation temperature (K)
59.9e6              ! heat of sublimation (J/Kg)

All units MKS.
The constituent information is needed for the backscattering model.
Erel is for chemical sputtering.
Vapor pressure coefficients are for thermal evaporation, also used in the time-dependent target temperature model.
Blackbody emissivity and heat of sublimation needed for target temperature time evolution.

