GENERAL NOTES:
Functions depending on target data are passed the target boundary cell index (denoted 'ibnd') and
the different material properties are deducted from the ibnd-th value of the relevant arrays.
'ibnd' is calculated by travelling along the mesh edge, starting in the North-West corner and going North,East,South,West. Corner cells, core boundary cells, dead cells, or diverted island core boundary cells are not included. We also assign a different segment number for each physically connected set of  wall cells. The mapping between (IX,IY) and (IBND) is kept in the XYMAP, IMPAX and IMPAY arrays.
XYMAP(IX,IY).eq.0 means the (IX,IY) cell is not a wall cell.
XYMAP(IX,IY).eq.IBNd meand the (IX,IY) cell is the (IBND)-th wall cell.
Reversely, the IBND-th cell maps to (IMAPX(IBND),IMAPY(IBND)).
The code reads/writes a new namelist 'b2.wall_save.namelist' containing these data.
Some related additional tallies are produced.
Two new stacks have been added to B2PLOT: a wall stack containing 1-D data along wall index, and a target stack containing 2-D data, where the first dimension is the wall index and the second is the depth profile within the target element. Both can be added to plots of B2 plasma data or plotted separately. Relevant matrix operations are included.

mod_wall:
---------
New wall data module. Contains hard-coded NDEPTH value. Needs 'DIMENSIONS.F'.
!!! May need to be shared with Eirene. !!!
Contains new wall material properties and temperature data.
Reads data from 'incatm' and 'Bulk_properties.[name]' and 'Surface_properties.[name]'.
Geometry data:
NBND = total number of wall cells.
NSEGMENTS = total number of segments.
NDEPTH = number of cell divisions inside the target segments.
IMAPREG = maps a wall cell to its B2 'ireg' number.
WALL_BEGIN = contains the wall cell index of the beginning of each segment. 
WALL_END = contains the wall cell index of the end of each segment.
Input/output data:
TARGET_TEMP = array containing the 2-D target temperature information  
BACKPLATE_TEMP = cooling temperature (default is given by the 'b2stbr_plate_temp' switch)
PLATE_THICKNESS = target element thickness (default is given by the 'b2stbr_plate_thick' switch)
PLATE_TIME_FACTOR = time multiplier for the temperature evolution in the target element (default 1.0)
Other Output arrays:
chemical_sputtering = Yield per species
physical_sputtering = Yield per species
physical_sputtering_energy = Yield per species
RES_sputtering = Yield per species
thermal_evaporation = Total evaporation flux 
backscattering = Fraction per species
backscattering_energy = Fraction per species

