Thanks, so, in a place that didn't matter,fortunately. I have now run my
16x24 (D-only) JET case with all the bells and whistles I could think
of, simultaneously and in full debug mode, i.e.: ExB drifts,
diamagnetics drifts, parallel or 21-moment viscosity, perpendicular
viscosity, new_df0 neutral transport, first flight model, ion_neutral
friction term, neutral flux limits, ballooning transport model, PFR
transport rescaling.
The code does run! Whether the results make sense is irrelevant here ;-)
The only problem the debugger gave me was with the PFR transport
rescaling, because the topcut(:), rightcut(:), bottomcut(:) and
leftcut(:) arrays did not have all their values defined (important for
topcut and the first two values must be defined for the others for the
test identifying if one is in a double-null PFR). The default values are
assigned and calculated in B2AG, but no carried over in the B2FGMTRY
file, not they need be. I fixed the problem by adding the default
definitions in alloc_b2mod_indirect as follows:

       bottomcut=nyd+1
       topcut   =-2
       rightcut =-2
       leftcut  =nxd+1

See
/afs/ipp/u/xpb/solps5.0_drifts/src/Braams/b2/src.local/b2mod_indirect.F .

I also cleaned up and removed my src.local.modules directory, and went
back to a formulation much closer to yours, and corrected the local
version of my Makefile accordingly. I checked it all works fine.

Now, I do not expect any of the changes we made in the last two days
could explain Fabio's crashes (unless his compiler did really strange
things), so I hope we'll hear something new from him on that.

Cheers,

Xavier.

