Hello David,

I had to answer the above question recently as Ralf decided that he
wanted to give some Xenon data (we have Xenon ADAS file in B2) to a
visitor from Karlsruhe for some collaboration with Konstantyn.
The short answer is that some part of the code can handle up to Z=50,
others up to Z=45, others only up to Z=20. So why not make it 54?
Fixing this didn't look so daunting, so Ralf happily volunteered me for
the job. Two days of hard work later, I now have a list of related
suggestions/improvements to the code for this purpose below. But first,
now that I can get a "b2frates" for Xenon, how do I make (if at all
possible), a decent looking "b2yr.plt" (mine has no labels anywhere),
and how do I view and print it properly (I only get the first page in
the PostScript)?

So, for the code changes:
- I modified 'ratadas.filelist' to go all the way to Xenon (Z=54). You
can find it in the ~xpb/solps5.0_drifts/data.local directory. Thanks for
creating that, by the way!
- More work was involved in completing 'ionization_potentials' (same
directory). I could find data for the whole table up to Z=30, but
afterwards it can become quite sketchy. I filled up the table with
dummies when I could find no data. I also updated the numbers in the
file, so that the data (where available) now is the same as is in the
latest CRC Handbook issue. Some more could be found on the NIST Web
Site.
- I had to increase 'rtnsmx' from 45 to 54 in 'b2cmrc.h'. To be found in
my src.local.
- In dhdata.F, I updated the SEQUA array to size 54 and added the
relevant elements, as well as a comment. Similar action taken in spect.F
for the SYMBOL and SYMBLL arrays.
- In spect.F, increased IZ0MAX to 54 and adapted relevant routine call
arguments and comments.
- In b2mod_b2plot.F, did the same to the "elements" array. to be found
in my src.local.modules.
- Same in b2mod_elements.F.
- In tallies.F, tucked the declaration of TIM_ARR inside a "#ifndef
NO_CDF" bracket.
- In b2mod_tallies.F, b2plot.F and b2mds.F, I updated the value of the
hydrogen ionization potential, and added the correction due to the
changed reduced mass for D and T. This required adding "use
b2mod_constants" at the top of b2mod_tallies.F. The code was also
generalized for multi-isotopic hydrogen mixtures, in the absence of the
"ionization_potentials" file.
- In b2yrdr.F, I removed the "dubious authorship" message when b2frates
is created using ADAS data.
- I also corrected ratads.F and spect.F so that, when building the UIDIN
name, the "/" after the $SOLPSTOP path would not be included twice.
- Lastly, in {sbb}/config/compiler.IBMaix, the block:
ifdef USE_EIRENE
LDLIBES += ${OBJECTCODE}/libeirene.a ${OBJECTCODE}/grlib.o
endif
is redundant and can be removed, as the overall Makefile in {sbb}
already contains:
ifdef USE_EIRENE
MNEXTRA=${OBJECTCODE}/libeirene.a ${OBJECTCODE}/grlib.o
endif

That's all for today,

