essentially turns off all rescaling!

- In the critical section where we apply the scaling to compute the B2
sources coming from neutral interaction processes, we are missing a
line:
   j = b2espcr(is)
(see line 1142 of the corrected routine in
~dpc/solps/solps5.0/src/Braams/b2/src/sources/eirene_mc.F).
This error means we were always rescaling (if at all) with the values
from the last species in the previous "j" loop.

- When dealing with the gas puff source, you were always using
USERFLUXPARM(ISTRAI,1). I changed this to TFLUX(ISTRAI), so that the gas
puff feedback schemes (which of course have time-dependent gas puff
source strengths) can also work with this.

- I figured how to include the volume recombination source rescaling
into your scheme. Basically, I condition the loop over the strata such
that, in the case of the recombination stratum, we do something on every
call, while for all other strata, we only rescale if Eirene has been
called. Please check this.

Xavier.

