b2.5:
-----
Hello David,

The debugger (while I was looking for siomething else) for a small
problem in the NGREAD routine. I traced it down to line 283, which
should read:
                iy=iy+nfluids(is)
instead of
                iy=iy+nfluids(is+1)

The context is that here Kukushkin's arrays are being transferred over
from the fort.44 file into b2plot quantities. IS is being looped of the
number of atomic species and IY is the index of that atomic species in
the SOLPS4.0 numbering (1:NS). NFLUIDS(IS) contains the numbers of fluid
species in B2 representing the homonuclear sequence of atomic species
IS. So the IY index has to jump over NFLUIDS(IS) species (and not
NFLUIDS(IS+1)) to get to the next atomic species.

Xavier.

